Important Fashion Industry Resources

Citadel Security has worked with the CFDA and is responsible for the security at the New York fashion week combined shows for the past 23 years. Founded in 1981 by a retired NYPD Detective Ty Yorio (read our interview with him) to provide Special Event Security, Trade Show Security, and Security Guards, Citadel has built a reputation as the go-to provider for security guard services in New York City. From private functions to fashion shows, escorts to doormen, Citadel Security provides its clients with professionalism, and reliability.

My Computer Tech is a local full-service computer repair store at 400 East 87th Street ((212) 828-1600) on the Upper East side of Manhattan. Avi Keller is the smartest and most knowledgeable computer repair man I have ever met and he is HONEST! I cannot recommend him too highly!
NameFace.com is an online service for event photographers, journalists and public relations agencies to name the celebrities, socialites and public personalities in photographs using facial recognition technology. Its totally revolutionary!! Now photographers will not need to ask you for your name at a party they will just "NameFace it".











